 if (rules != null)  KIPP Through College (KTC)is a college access program designed to support KIPP Charlotte alumni in high school as they work their way to and through college. Beginning in the summer before their 9th grade year, students will meet with their KTC advisor (whom they begin working with in 7th and 8th grade during the high school placement process) to ensure their success in high school and to prepare them for college admission, matriculation, and graduation. In addition, throughout their high school experiences, KIPP Charlotte alumni have the opportunity to return to KIPP Charlotte for community service, tutoring from area college students, and to attend college tours.KIPP Charlotte is extremely proud of our two classes of alumni, the Prides of 2015 and 2016. Alumni gained admission to various high schools around the country. These alumni now attend the following high schools:Cannon SchoolCarolina International SchoolCharlotte Country DayCharlotte LatinChrist School (Arden, NC)Davidson Day SchoolDeerfield Academy (Deerfield, MA)East Mecklenburg High SchoolGray Stone Day SchoolHarding University High SchoolKennedy CharterMallard Creek High SchoolMarie G. Davis Military & Global Leadership AcademyNorthwest School of the ArtsPhillip O. Berry Academy of TechnologyProvidence Day SchoolQueens Grant Community SchoolRocky River High SchoolSouthern Lee High School (SC)Vance High SchoolWest Charlotte IBWest Mecklenburg High SchoolKIPP Change Academy (K-4)5431 Hickory Grove RoadCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 209-9944KIPP Academy Charlotte (5-8)931 Wilann DriveCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 537-2044KIPP CharlotteFacebookTwitterLinkedinMailpowered by Educational Networks//proxyKiller();var curWindowOnLoad = window.onload;
