 if (rules != null)  What is High School Placement?The first phase of the KIPP Through College program is High School Placement (HSP). The role of HSP is to assist our families with the process of selecting and applying to high school, as KIPP Charlotte is currently only a 5-8 program. We build strong relationships with high schools (public and private) in Charlotte, as well as boarding schools around North Carolina and the East Coast. We work hard to make the process as clear and efficient as possible for families and students and our goal is for each student to be placed in the best fit school for their personal goals and strengths as an individual.For students and families interested in applying to private schools, there are several key components that schools use in the admissions process. Schools evaluate students based on:Grades (typically from 6th-8th grade)Standardized test scores (EOG scores, ISEE or SSAT)Student involvement in activities (sports, clubs, music, religious groups, etc.)Teacher recommendations (must have 8th grade ELA and math teachers, others are optional)Student essay/applicationFamilys Role:Commit to learning about all high school optionsStay informed about all paperwork, deadlines, and eventsComplete applications, forms, and financial aid information and return them promptlyStay involved in the application process by attending meetings and counseling your studentHigh School Placement Timeline7th grade:High School Placement class each FridayOne on one meetings with family and HSP contactFamilies begin to research high schools and learn about admission requirementsStudents on path to private schools take practice SSAT in spring8th grade:AugustParents and students select their five top high school choicesParents and students receive academic performance summarySeptemberHSP Manager, Staff, and School Leader recommend schools for each student based on academic performance summary and family choiceFamilies register for ISEE and SSAT exams (if applying to private schools)Attend HS Information Fair (at KIPP) September 27thAttend open houses at high schoolsStudents start studying for ISEE/SSAT exams (private schools)OctoberStudent and parent portions of applications are due (private schools)Continue attending open housesSet up half-day shadow visits (private schools)Students continue studying for ISEE/SSAT exams (private schools)NovemberStudents attend half-day visits (private schools)Teachers complete recommendationsStudents continue studying for ISEE/SSAT testing (private schools)DecemberStudents take the ISEE and SSAT exams (private schools)Families reactivate CMS ID number (if applicable) to enroll in Magnet LotteryFamilies complete charter school applications for lotteriesJanuaryFamilies complete federal tax forms and submit copies to financial aid offices (private schools)Families complete financial aid packets for boarding and private schoolsMagnet school lottery for CMSStudents audition for Northwest School of the ArtsMarchBoarding schools select freshman class, notifications sent out March 10thFinancial aid decisions are mailed to students and parentsApril/MayCharlotte area private schools release acceptancesStudents, parents and HSP manager review acceptancesStudents and parents select the best high school to meet family needs and desiresStudents and parents complete acceptance paperwork, send in deposits (private schools)8th grade KIPP to College Parent MeetingIf you have any questions regarding the high school placement process, please contact:Claudia OllivierreDirector of KIPP Through Collegecollivierre@kippcharlotte.org980.297.4714KIPP Change Academy (K-4)5431 Hickory Grove RoadCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 209-9944KIPP Academy Charlotte (5-8)931 Wilann DriveCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 537-2044KIPP CharlotteFacebookTwitterLinkedinMailpowered by Educational Networks//proxyKiller();var curWindowOnLoad = window.onload;
