 img.enlarge  Back to topNews and AnnouncementsHigh School Information Session on October 15th at KIPP Academy CharlotteFor the Pride of 2024 students and families, KIPP Through College is hosting a High School Information Session to learn about high school options and the transition.Pride of 2024 students and families -Please join KIPP Through College's Director, Claudia Perry, and Associate Director, Tamiko Lockett, for an information session on the Charlotte - Mecklenburg High School system and what families can expect as their children make the transition to college. For all Pride of 2024 students and families, this event will help you decide on high school and navigate the applications for the best high schools in the CMS system.What?: What's the 411 - an Information Session on High SchoolWho?: Pride of 2024 students and familiesWhen? Tuesday, October 15th at 6:00pmWhere?: KIPP Academy Charlotte CafegymatoriumAnd don't forget that the window for first round applications for magnet high schools in CMS is already open and will remain open until November 25th!https://www.wearecms.com/apps/pages/index.jsp...KIPP Change Academy (K-4)5431 Hickory Grove RoadCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 209-9944KIPP Academy Charlotte (5-8)931 Wilann DriveCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 537-2044KIPP CharlotteFacebookTwitterLinkedinMailpowered by Educational Networks//proxyKiller();var curWindowOnLoad = window.onload;
