 img.enlarge  Back to topNews and AnnouncementsKIPP Change Academy Dance Team featured on QC Life morning showThe KCA Dance Team led by Annalise Coleman was featured this morning on QC Life showing off their latest dance routine and promoting "An Evening with Steve Smith Sr" on November 18th.This morning, QC Life hosted the KCA Dance Team and KCA Principal Malcolm Brooks as they showed off their newest routine. These amazing students are led by Dance Teacher Annalise Coleman and represent both the Prides of 2029 and 2030. They absolutely charmed the anchor, Christine Sperow.The KCA Dance Team is also set to perform at "An Evening with Steve Smith Sr" on November 18th from 5:30 - 8:30pm. Being held at the Collector's Room in the South End, tickets are $150 and include drinks, hors d'oeuvres, raffle prizes, and a presentation from former Panthers player, Steve Smith.To meet Steve Smith and support the KIPP Charlotte Lions, you can find tickets here: https://conta.cc/35EsuGxIf you're not able to attend, you can donate here: http://bit.ly/31qygrUWe hope to see you there!https://www.queencityweekend.com/steve-smith-...KIPP Change Academy (K-4)5431 Hickory Grove RoadCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 209-9944KIPP Academy Charlotte (5-8)931 Wilann DriveCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 537-2044KIPP CharlotteFacebookTwitterLinkedinMailpowered by Educational Networks//proxyKiller();var curWindowOnLoad = window.onload;
