 if (rules != null)  The KIPP Through College office at KIPP Charlotte offers many services for KIPPsters and their families.The first phase of the KIPP Through College program isHigh School Placement(HSP). The role of HSP is to assist families with the process of selecting and applying to high schools. For more information on High School Placement,click here.The next phase of KIPP Through College is a college access program designed to support KIPP Charlotte alumni in high school as they work towards college matriculation. For more information onKIPP Through College alumni services,click here.For more information on High School Placement and KIPP Through College, please contactClaudia Ollivierre,Director of KIPP Through College, at980.297.4714orcollivierre@kippcharlotte.org.KIPP Change Academy (K-4)5431 Hickory Grove RoadCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 209-9944KIPP Academy Charlotte (5-8)931 Wilann DriveCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 537-2044KIPP CharlotteFacebookTwitterLinkedinMailpowered by Educational Networks//proxyKiller();var curWindowOnLoad = window.onload;
