 img.enlarge  try   catch (e)  Frequently Asked QuestionsGeneral QuestionsQ: Where are the schools located?KIPP Change Academy (grades K-5)is located at 5431 Hickory Grove Road.KIPP Academy Charlotte (grades 6-8)is located at 931 Wilann Dr. Charlotte, NC, 28215.Q: What are school hours?KIPP Change AcademyMonday - Thursday, 8:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m.Friday, 8:00 a.m. - 2:30 p.m.KIPP Academy Charlotte:Monday - Thursday,8:15a.m. - 4:15 p.m.Friday, 8:15a.m. - 2:45p.m.Q: How can I get involved at the school?A:Please contactVanessa Sanchezatvsanchez@kippcharlotte.org, orclick hereto find out about current volunteer opportunities. Please view our wish list if you are interested in donating supplies or materials. Click support KIPP at the top of this page if you wish to support KIPP Charlotte financially. We truly appreciate any form of involvement!Q: What classes do students take?A:Reading, Math, Science, Social Studies, Gym/Health, Art and Writing. Classes vary by grade level.Q: Do you have a Student and Parent Handbook?A:Yes, and the handbook for each school can be found on the respective school page:KIPP Academy Charlotte (Grades 6-8)KIPP Change Academy (Grades K-5)For ParentsQ: Is summer school mandatory?A:Yes. To be enrolled for the school year all students must attend the summer session or their place will be offered to a student on the waiting list.Q: What is the dress code?A:In order to ensure that the focus is on learning, students must abide by the dress code. The KIPP Charlotte uniform consists of a KIPP Charlotte polo shirt, t-shirt and/or sweatshirt, or a college t-shirt or sweatshirt; khaki pants; a brown or black belt; black, brown, or white shoes (soles and shoelaces must be the same color as the shoes); and white, black, blue or brown socks. Students may not wear hooded sweatshirts or zippered jackets when they are inside the classroom. Students may wear khaki skirts, capris, or shorts that are at least knee length. Hats, scarves, gloves, jackets, etc. may be worn when transitioning outside, but must be removed inside. Earrings larger than a quarter are not allowed. Necklaces and rosaries worn outside of the shirt are not allowed. Hair picks, brushes, combs or other health/beauty products are not allowed.Q: Where can students purchase extra uniform shirts?A:In the main office before, after, or during (with permission) school hours.Q: What meals does the school provide?A:Free breakfast and lunch are provided for all students.Q: What school supplies does my child need?A:All students need to come on the first day with 2 pencils and a book bag. The rest will be provided by the school.KIPP Change Academy (K-4)5431 Hickory Grove RoadCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 209-9944KIPP Academy Charlotte (5-8)931 Wilann DriveCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 537-2044KIPP CharlotteFacebookTwitterLinkedinMailpowered by Educational Networks//proxyKiller();var curWindowOnLoad = window.onload;
