 if (rules != null)  #thisDiv  KIPP Change Academy is a college preparatory public charter school in Charlotte, NCthat opened in2016 currently serving grades K, 1, 2, 4, and 5 andwe will addadditional grades until we are fully grown(K-5); Our rising 6th grade students will automatically transition to KIPP Academy Charlotte Middle School.At KIPP Change Academy, we commit to developing the whole child through culturally responsive teaching that cultivates confidence and a positive self-identity. We believe that self-efficacy leads to creativity, risk taking, and critical thinking. Students will believe they can grow their character and intellect. These skills will provide our students the opportunity to make a profound impact in their community and world at large. What makes KCA special: More time learning (8 to 4 p.m.) Daily small-groups in math and reading High expectations for behavior and academic success KIPP Through College program supports kids from K through college graduation Free transportation STEM Class Dance Art Music Production Project-based and service learning opportunitiesPlease click below to sign up for our free transportation:To purchase uniforms, please visit us at 5431 Hickory Grove Rd. Charlotte, NC 282155431 Hickory Grove Rd.Charlotte, NC 28215Phone (704) 209-9944Fax (704) 527-2855KIPP Change Academy (K-4)5431 Hickory Grove RoadCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 209-9944KIPP Academy Charlotte (5-8)931 Wilann DriveCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 537-2044KIPP CharlotteFacebookTwitterLinkedinMailpowered by Educational Networks//proxyKiller();var curWindowOnLoad = window.onload;
