 img.enlarge  try   catch (e)  Employment OpportunitiesExtraordinary TeachersfromKIPP FoundationonVimeo.At KIPP, we dont measure success only by test scores but by the number of students who are achieving their dreams in college and beyond. With a goal that big, we need educators and staff who have the motivation, drive, compassion, and commitment to ensure that all students reach their full potential.Click to see current employment opportunities and apply onlineWe are always interested in hearing from K-8 teachers who have the passion, devotion, and tenacity necessary to help make our schools extraordinary. Preference will be given to licensed, highly qualified teachers.The ProgramKIPP Charlotte is a member of the acclaimed Knowledge is Power Program (KIPP), a national network of 224 free, open-enrollment, college-preparatory public schools dedicated to preparing students in underserved communities for success in college and in life. Parents, students, and teachers sign a contract that spells out the expectations of being part of the KIPP Team and Family. Our well-structured reward and discipline program ensures that students meet these expectations.In the fall of 2007, KIPP Charlotte opened its doors to its first class of 90 fifth graders. The school now serves 800 students in grades K-8. The mission of KIPP Charlotte is to prepare all of our students to thrive in the nations finest high schools and colleges by cultivating the habits of mind, character skills, and knowledge necessary for their success. We will provide an education which enables them to lead full lives and will empower our students to be the future leaders of Charlotte and agents of change in the world beyond.If there is a problem, we look for a solution.If there is a better way, we find it.If a teammate needs help, we give.If we need help, we ask.What if you worked at KIPP Charlotte?Commit to a bold mission: college graduation for all.Were raising the bar for the definition of success for children in low-income communities: its not just getting to college, but rather, seeing them all the way through to the day they graduate.Grow your career.Through our KIPP School Leadership Programs, we develop leaders through our multi-tiered leadership development. At KIPP, we believe that the work of educators is incredibly complex and challenging, and we approach professional development of educators with the utmost intentionality.Innovate and do whats best for students.At KIPP Charlotte, we want our teachers and leaders to make decisions based on the needs of students, so we foster a culture of data-driven instruction and encourage teachers to bring their interests and passions into the schools. Teachers have used their photography interests to beautify our schools, began dance teams, and implemented Hispanic Heritage Month to celebrate our students' cultures.Share with colleagues who hold the same high expectations.We dont teach or lead alone. KIPP Charlotte teachers are part of a team in 224 KIPP schools coast to coast, united in the same mission: to ensure that our students are going to and through college.Focus on character and academics.KIPP Charlottes mottoWork hard. Be good. Think.isnt just a tagline. We believe that for KIPPsters to truly be successful adults, they will need character strengths such as service, excellence, integrity, passion, courage, and leadership in addition to a rigorous academic curriculum.Apply NowPositions will be filled on a rolling basis; applicants are strongly encouraged to apply immediately.Assign yourself. Build a better tomorrow. Join the Pride.KIPP Change Academy (K-4)5431 Hickory Grove RoadCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 209-9944KIPP Academy Charlotte (5-8)931 Wilann DriveCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 537-2044KIPP CharlotteFacebookTwitterLinkedinMailpowered by Educational Networks//proxyKiller();var curWindowOnLoad = window.onload;
