 if (rules != null)  At KIPP Charlotte schools, we refer to our students, parents, school leaders, teachers, and staff asour Pride.Our Pride is the community that works hard every day to ensure our students can climb the mountain to and through college, lead choice-filled lives, and become future leaders of Charlotte and the world beyond.KIPP Charlotte schools are tuition-free and open to all in grades K-8. We would love for you to join our Pride!ENROLL NOWHOW TO APPLYKIPP Charlotte accepts applications on a rolling basis through an online enrollment system,SchoolMint. It takes just three steps to apply:Visit theKIPP Charlotte SchoolMint pageand create an accountComplete a profile for yourself and an additional parent or guardianAnswer a few questions about your student(s)ENROLLMENT PROCESSApplications for the current school year (2020-21) and the upcoming school year (2021-22) are now available. If the number of applications for the upcoming school year exceeds capacity, KIPP Charlotte will hold a lottery for initial enrollment.Post-Lottery EnrollmentOnce the lottery date has passed, KIPP Charlotte will continue to accept applications throughout the year. Students are accepted on a first come, first served basis as seats are available. When a grade level has reached capacity, students will be placed on a waitlist.VISIT OUR SCHOOLSInterested in visitingKIPP Change AcademyorKIPP Academy Charlotte? We frequently update our Facebook page with open house dates. You can also contact our schools directly to schedule a visit.To visit KIPP Change Academy, call:704-209-9944To visit KIPP Academy Charlotte, call:704-537-2044MORE INFORMATIONIf you have questions about the enrollment process forKIPP Change Academy (Grades K-4), please contact Ms. Dwan Rankin at (704) 232-6183. For questions about KIPP Academy Charlotte (Grades 5-8), please contact Ms. Sara-Kathryn Ferrell at (980) 297-3679.ENROLL NOWKIPP Change Academy (K-4)5431 Hickory Grove RoadCharlotte, NC 28215Phone: (704) 